{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"sun-snout-ledge","assignee":"claude","description":"## Why\n\nThe README is a thorough ~31KB reference (Why / Requirements / Install / CLI /\nPython / MCP / Config / Tests) but has **no short tutorial** — Install jumps\nstraight into reference-style command docs. A newcomer has no golden path from\nzero to a working first flow. Meanwhile `rebar --help` already emits a full,\nauthoritative command index backed by 40 per-command help files, so a separate\n\"cheat sheet\" would only duplicate it and invite drift.\n\n## What\n\nAdd a single, single-sourced `## Quickstart` section near the top of `README.md`:\n\n- Install (one canonical line) -> `rebar init` -> create a first ticket ->\n  `ready` / `claim` -> close, showing **expected output** at each step.\n- A minimal \"point an agent at it\" example (the MCP one-liner) so the agent path\n  is visible.\n- Uses only the ~6 core commands inline and **defers the full command list to\n  `rebar --help`** rather than re-listing commands.\n\n## Scope\n\n`README.md` only (one new section + a link to it from the top). Explicitly NOT a\nseparate cheat-sheet doc and NOT a duplicate command index — `rebar --help` +\nthe `_cli/help/*.txt` files remain the authoritative command reference. Keep it\nshort (a screenful).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `README.md` has a `## Quickstart` section near the top with an\n  install -> first-ticket -> first-agent-flow walkthrough and expected output.\n- [ ] It shows only the core commands inline and points to `rebar --help` for the\n  full list (no re-listed command index, no separate cheat-sheet file).\n- [ ] The commands shown are copy-pasteable and correct against the current CLI.\n- [ ] A top-of-README link points to the Quickstart.","id":"3bf6-de76-bdd4-4096","parent_id":"b02d-10bc-07ee-49e7","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Add a single-sourced README Quickstart (golden path; defers to rebar --help)"},"env_id":"58e9f32e-f999-436d-9c1a-5d0eef5c9903","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783148934216858602,"uuid":"567815f9-0912-448c-b285-4cd90c042316"}